@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="privacy-policy">
    <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</p>
    
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>This Privacy Policy describes how your personal information is collected, used, and shared when you visit this blog (the "Site").</p>
    
    <h2>Information Collection</h2>
    <p>When you visit the Site, I automatically collect certain information about your device, including information about your web browser, IP address, time zone, and some of the cookies that are installed on your device. This is referred to as "Device Information."</p>
    
    <p>I collect Device Information using the following technologies:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>"Cookies" are data files placed on your device or computer and often include an anonymous unique identifier.</li>
        <li>"Log files" track actions occurring on the Site, and collect data including your IP address, browser type, Internet service provider, referring/exit pages, and date/time stamps.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>How I Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>I use the Device Information collected to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Improve and optimize the Site (for example, by generating analytics about how visitors browse)</li>
        <li>Assess the success of my marketing and content efforts</li>
        <li>Protect the Site from malicious activity</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Sharing Your Information</h2>
    <p>I do not share, sell, rent, or trade your information with third parties for their commercial purposes. I may share information with third party service providers that help me operate the Site (such as hosting services).</p>
    <p>I may also release information when its release is appropriate to comply with the law, enforce site policies, or protect my or others' rights, property, or safety.</p>
    
    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>This blog may use third-party services such as Google Analytics. These services may collect information sent by your browser as part of a web page request, such as cookies or your IP address. Their collection and use of information is governed by their respective privacy policies.</p>
    
    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>If you are a European resident, you have the right to access personal information I hold about you and to ask that this information be corrected, updated, or deleted. Please contact me with such requests.</p>
    
    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>Device Information collected through the Site is maintained indefinitely for analytical and security purposes.</p>
    
    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>I may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in my practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons.</p>
    
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For more information about my privacy practices, if you have questions, or if you would like to make a complaint, please contact me by email.</p>
</div>
